them to lead our company?

72
00:04:41,698 --> 00:04:42,699
Copy that.

73
00:04:43,491 --> 00:04:44,659
Let's put our hands in a circle.

74
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:45,827
- Come on.
- Hurry.

75
00:04:45,910 --> 00:04:47,036
Alright, listen up.

76
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:48,663
Whoever matches with my hand
will be the spokesperson.

77
00:04:48,746 --> 00:04:50,748
- Let's include Baldo.
- Okay, one more time.

78
00:04:50,832 --> 00:04:53,293
So, where were we, Walter?

79
00:04:53,376 --> 00:04:54,836
Uh... Me?

80
00:04:56,462 --> 00:04:59,173
Well, since you're
already standing,

81
00:04:59,257 --> 00:05:02,385
is there anything you want to
improve in the management?

82
00:05:02,468 --> 00:05:08,516
Um, we were thinking,
BMC, that it'll be better if...

83
00:05:08,599 --> 00:05:10,643
- Yes, we...
- Boss.

84
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:11,936
I have a proposal.

85
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:17,942
[PLAYFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

86
00:05:18,026 --> 00:05:21,529
Nora, put all the bottles of
scotch and whiskey in that box.

87
00:05:21,612 --> 00:05:24,574
And put all the bottles of wine
in the other box.

88
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:26,075
Okay?

89
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:28,036
Susan, put all the bottles
of beer in there.

90
00:05:29,495 --> 00:05:30,621
Handle them with care.

91
