form of temptation?

99
00:05:54,270 --> 00:05:55,605
So, you know now, huh?

100
00:05:56,647 --> 00:05:57,982
Are you mad?

101
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:01,402
- [GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SIGHS DEEPLY]

102
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:04,781
Carlota, you should've
told me about this.

103
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:08,659
I'm their father.

104
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:11,996
I should know those things.

105
00:06:13,164 --> 00:06:16,292
Lovey, had you known then,

106
00:06:16,375 --> 00:06:18,920
would you have helped Cyrus

107
00:06:19,003 --> 00:06:20,755
despite how angry
you were with him?

108
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:27,011
I'm not blaming you.

109
00:06:28,679 --> 00:06:30,014
Things happen.

110
00:06:31,641 --> 00:06:33,351
But we are a team.

111
00:06:33,434 --> 00:06:34,769
You know that, right?

112
00:06:34,852 --> 00:06:41,859
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

113
00:06:43,861 --> 00:06:44,904
[SMOOCHES]

114
00:06:46,197 --> 00:06:47,532
One last thing, boss,

115
00:06:47,615 --> 00:06:50,493
I hope during weekends
or beyond office hours,

116
00:06:50,576 --> 00:06:53,079
we refrain from sending emails
or making calls to each other.

117
00:06:53,162 --> 00:06:55,915
Work-life balance is
also important, you know.

118
00:06:55,998 --> 00:06:57,792
That's why I make
so many mistakes.

119
00:06:57,875 --> 00:07:00,920
We're more productive
when our minds are well-rested.

120
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:05,299
Okay, I'll consider this.

121
00:07:05,383 --> 00:07:08,344
Boss, I also hope we can
have a mental health day

122
00:07:08,427 --> 00:07:09,846
at least once a month.

123
00:07:09,929 --> 00:07:12,306
Work can drive us crazy,

124
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:14,559
especially when we have
a demanding boss.

125
00:07:14,642 --> 00:07:16,435
[PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

126
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:18,354
Wait, which department
are you from again?

127
00:07:18,437 --> 00:07:19,689
She's from Sir Philip's office.

128
00:07:20,815 --> 00:07:22,233
Then what are you doing here?

129
00:07:22,316 --> 00:07:23,776
[CHUCKLES]
It's Sec. Kim's farewell...

130
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:25,111
I second the motion.

131
00:07:25,194 --> 00:07:27,196
I agree with everything
Steph said.

132
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:29,157
[CHUCKLING AWKWARDLY]

133
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,616
[BRANDON]
Okay, just to be clear,

134
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:33,244
everyone here shares
the same sentiments, right?

135
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:37,915
I want a mentorship program
for new hires like me.

136
00:07:37,999 --> 00:07:40,543
BMC, if it's possible,

137
00:07:40,626 --> 00:07:45,006
I hope we can offer free shuttle
services for our employees

138
00:07:45,089 --> 00:07:47,466
since not everyone's
allowed to get car loans

139
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:49,886
and public transportation
is also expensive these days.

140
00:07:51,596 --> 00:07:53,055
- Okay.
- That way, we'll be fresh

141
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:54,473
in the morning, just like you.

142
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:56,601
[PLAYFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

143
00:07:56,684 --> 00:07:59,562
[CHUCKLING AWKWARDLY]

144
00:07:59,645 --> 00:08:02,773
- [UTENSILS CLATTER]
- Dad.

145
00:08:02,857 --> 00:08:04,859
They asked me to go to
the Marketing department.

146
00:08:04,942 --> 00:08:06,861
I think they just want
my approval

147
00:08:06,944 --> 00:08:08,863
for the IdeaEx event.

148
00:08:08,946 --> 00:08:11,449
Oh, okay.

149
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:14,493
I'll take you there.
I'm going to head out anyway.

150
00:08:15,703 --> 00:08:17,997
Uh, you can go with me.

151
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:20,208
I'm going to the office, too.

152
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:21,626
What for?

153
00:08:21,709 --> 00:08:23,252
Y-You know, just stuff.

154
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:26,422
- Because we have to work on...
- I know!

155
00:08:26,505 --> 00:08:29,091
Why don't we go together?
All three of us!

156
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:31,344
Mom, Dad, I-I can drive myself.

157
00:08:31,427 --> 00:08:33,679
Just tell me who I need
to talk to when I get there.

158
00:08:33,763 --> 00:08:35,848
No, we are going with you.

159
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:37,308
That's final.

160
00:08:37,808 --> 00:08:38,809
Ma.

161
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:41,646
I feel like an elementary
school student

162
00:08:41,729 --> 00:08:43,397
with my mom and dad
dropping me off.

163
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:45,274
- [CHUCKLES]
- [CARLOTA] Cyrus.

164
00:08:45,358 --> 00:08:46,525
When you were kids,

165
00:08:46,609 --> 00:08:49,028
I was the only one
dropping you off at school.

166
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:51,322
- [QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]
- Your dad never did.

167
00:08:51,405 --> 00:08:53,699
Come on, Lovey.
You're exposing me.

168
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:55,493
Well, it's true!

169
00:08:55,576 --> 00:08:59,163
- I'm only saying the truth.
- Mom.

170
00:08:59,247 --> 00:09:03,960
- Stop exposing Dad. [CHUCKLES]
- Okay. Fine.

171
00:09:04,043 --> 00:09:05,336
Let's eat!

172
00:09:05,419 --> 00:09:07,588
So, what do you guys think?

173
00:09:07,672 --> 00:09:10,591
Um, some of their requests
are feasible.

174
00:09:10,675 --> 00:09:14,637
But we still need to
discuss the other ones.

175
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:18,099
Okay. Let's prioritize the one
about mental health.

176
00:09:18,182 --> 00:09:20,768
Make sure we have a therapist
on standby 24/7,

177
00:09:20,851 --> 00:09:24,272
who can do one-on-one sessions
with anyone who needs it.

178
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:26,399
Noted, Boss Idol.

179
00:09:26,482 --> 00:09:27,650
- Okay.
- See you.

180
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:32,405
- [INHALES DEEPLY]
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]

181
00:09:34,031 --> 00:09:35,032
Why?

182
00:09:36,325 --> 00:09:38,411
Uh, it's nothing.

183
00:09:39,870 --> 00:09:42,415
So, you do know
how to listen, boss.

184
00:09:42,498 --> 00:09:43,791
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

185
00:09:43,874 --> 00:09:47,962
Sec. Kim, we've been
working together for nine years.

186
00:09:48,045 --> 00:09:51,716
