I take care of people...

187
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:55,636
...who are important to me.

188
00:09:55,720 --> 00:10:02,727
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

189
00:10:04,770 --> 00:10:06,105
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

190
00:10:07,815 --> 00:10:09,108
Uh, alright.

191
00:10:13,654 --> 00:10:15,406
- Good morning.
- Madam.

192
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:17,491
Chairman, we are very
honored to have you here.

193
00:10:17,575 --> 00:10:21,704
Oh! You've lost weight. Why?

194
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:23,748
How's Laura?

195
00:10:23,831 --> 00:10:25,082
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

196
00:10:25,166 --> 00:10:27,168
W-We... Still my ex-wife.

197
00:10:27,251 --> 00:10:29,503
Oh, don't pout. Don't pout.

198
00:10:29,587 --> 00:10:33,049
I have a strong feeling
that you'll get back together.

199
00:10:33,132 --> 00:10:35,176
- [CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
- I'm sorry, Philip.

200
00:10:35,259 --> 00:10:38,387
I tried to convince them
not to come, but they insisted.

201
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:39,847
No, it's okay, sir.

202
00:10:39,930 --> 00:10:43,100
I'm sure they are also
excited to see your AVP.

203
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:44,769
Oh, yes, we are.

204
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:45,811
Philip.

205
00:10:45,895 --> 00:10:47,855
- Chairman.
- Oh, thank you.

206
00:10:47,938 --> 00:10:49,231
- Sir Cyrus.
- Thank you.

207
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:51,317
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

208
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,443
Guys.

209
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:57,156
Okay. So, I've given my inputs

210
00:10:57,239 --> 00:10:59,450
regarding all your concerns
to the HR department.

211
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:02,161
And now, it's up to Roni and
the whole HR department

212
00:11:02,244 --> 00:11:03,704
to implement it.

213
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:06,707
Kim Marie, coordinate closely
with Roni regarding this.

214
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:08,709
I want daily updates.

215
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:13,464
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

216
00:11:13,547 --> 00:11:14,757
Yes, boss.

217
00:11:16,092 --> 00:11:17,968
Okay, good.

218
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:20,888
So, what's next?

219
00:11:20,971 --> 00:11:23,474
- [CLAPS]
- It's time for...

220
00:11:23,557 --> 00:11:24,767
Heart Hunting!

221
00:11:24,850 --> 00:11:26,769
- [CLAPPING]
- [CHEERING]

222
00:11:26,852 --> 00:11:30,272
[JORDY] Yes! Yes! Heart Hunting!

223
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:33,359
D-Did I just hear "heart"?

224
00:11:33,442 --> 00:11:37,154
Okay, are you all ready
to hunt hearts?

225
00:11:37,238 --> 00:11:39,698
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

226
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:42,451
Okay, so here are the mechanics
of the game.

227
00:11:42,535 --> 00:11:44,078
[WALTER] Each one of you

228
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:48,624
will pick one heart puzzle piece
from this bucket.

229
00:11:48,707 --> 00:11:52,211
Your first mission is
to find your other half.

230
00:11:52,294 --> 00:11:55,798
They'll be your teammate
for this game.

231
00:11:55,881 --> 00:11:57,174
As you can see,

232
00:11:57,258 --> 00:12:00,553
the hearts you're holding
are not yet complete

233
00:12:00,636 --> 00:12:06,350
because your goal is to find
the final missing piece

234
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:08,436
of the hearts

235
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:10,271
that you're holding.

236
00:12:10,354 --> 00:12:11,355
Okay?

237
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:15,943
The first pair to complete
the heart wins the game.

238
00:12:16,026 --> 00:12:19,155
- Yeah!
- Let's go!

239
00:12:19,238 --> 00:12:22,992
[WALTER] Okay, I know
we went through a lot today.

240
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:24,660
Our minds are a bit tired.

241
00:12:24,743 --> 00:12:27,455
So, if you have questions
about the mechanics,

242
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:28,956
just ask me, okay?

243
00:12:29,039 --> 00:12:30,458
- Okay!
- What's your question?

244
00:12:30,541 --> 00:12:32,918
- Uh, Jordy.
- Oh. Yes, boss?

245
00:12:33,002 --> 00:12:36,839
I want to propose a trade.
Your puzzle piece for mine.

246
00:12:36,922 --> 00:12:39,133
- Why?
- [QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

247
00:12:39,216 --> 00:12:41,218
I need to talk to Sec. Kim.

248
00:12:43,512 --> 00:12:46,432
R-Regarding our meeting
with the Park Group.

249
00:12:46,515 --> 00:12:47,600
Oh. [CHUCKLES]

250
00:12:47,683 --> 00:12:49,810
I thought you didn't want
Steph as your teammate.

251
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:52,146
She's alright, boss. You just
have to get used to her.

252
00:12:52,229 --> 00:12:55,399
Okay. Then, what do you propose?
What do you want?

253
00:12:55,483 --> 00:12:57,359
It's on the house, boss.

254
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:59,945
If you need someone
when Sir Philip's not around,

255
00:13:00,029 --> 00:13:01,280
I'm always here.

256
00:13:01,363 --> 00:13:03,491
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

257
00:13:03,574 --> 00:13:06,994
Uh... [CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]
I'm just joking.

258
00:13:07,077 --> 00:13:09,788
[SNICKERS] Calm down, Jordy.

259
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:10,873
Deal.

260
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:13,792
[CHUCKLES] Deal.

261
00:13:16,962 --> 00:13:19,590
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

262
00:13:19,673 --> 00:13:22,510
[BRANDON] Oh, um, I guess
we're on the same team?

263
00:13:24,053 --> 00:13:25,054
U-Uh...

264
00:13:26,847 --> 00:13:29,141
That wasn't the piece
you picked earlier, right?

265
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:33,020
So, you were paying attention
to my heart?

266
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:35,272
What?

267
00:13:35,356 --> 00:13:36,649
N-Not at all.

268
00:13:36,732 --> 00:13:38,442
U-Um, I...

269
00:13:38,526 --> 00:13:40,319
I just...

270
00:13:40,402 --> 00:13:43,072
I accidentally saw it earlier.

271
00:13:44,698 --> 00:13:47,576
We're not allowed
to swap hearts, right?

272
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:50,955
Well, no one mentioned that
in the rules.

273
00:13:51,038 --> 00:13:54,375
Oh, so someone agreed
to swap with you?

274
00:13:55,543 --> 00:13:57,419
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

275
00:13:57,503 --> 00:14:00,965
I'm an expert at closing deals,
remember?

276
00:14:02,216 --> 00:14:03,801
Hmm.

277
00:14:03,884 --> 00:14:05,970
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

278
00:14:06,053 --> 00:14:07,263
Okay.

279
00:14:07,346 --> 00:14:08,472
- Are you good?
- Yeah!

280
00:14:08,556 --> 00:14:10,099
- Are you all ready?
- Super!

281
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:12,518
- Are you all excited?
- Let's do this!

282
00:14:12,601 --> 00:14:13,978
- Yeah!
- Okay.

283
00:14:14,061 --> 00:14:18,274
So, we'll find out which
lovely pair will win later.

284
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:20,985
- So, in three...
- And to spice things up...

285
00:14:21,068 --> 00:14:23,612
the first team who gets
to complete their puzzle

286
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:25,197
will win a tablet.

287
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:28,826
[SHRIEKING]

288
00:14:28,909 --> 00:14:31,078
- [WALTER] Okay, so...
- Calm down.

289
00:14:31,161 --> 00:14:32,580
Let's begin!

290
00:14:32,663 --> 00:14:35,332
We'll find out who
our lovely pairs are

291
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:39,253
in three, two...
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

292
00:14:39,336 --> 00:14:40,713
Go!

293
00:14:40,796 --> 00:14:43,549
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

294
00:14:43,632 --> 00:14:45,759
[BLOWING WHISTLE]

295
00:14:46,427 --> 00:14:48,596
- [LEAVES RUSTLING]
- If I were Sir Walter,

296
00:14:48,679 --> 00:14:51,515
where would I hide
the puzzle piece?

297
00:14:52,808 --> 00:14:55,060
You know, when it comes
to Sir Walter,

298
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:56,645
expect the unexpected.

299
00:14:56,729 --> 00:14:58,439
Whatever. You're a cheater.

300
00:14:58,522 --> 00:15:01,108
I saw you swapping
hearts with our boss.

301
00:15:01,191 --> 00:15:04,486
What do you mean?
There's no rule against it.

302
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:07,448
Besides, don't you want me
as your teammate?

303
00:15:07,531 --> 00:15:09,575
Hmm, just so-so.

304
00:15:09,658 --> 00:15:11,327
"Just so-so"?

305
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:13,829
Really? That's all I get?

306
00:15:13,912 --> 00:15:16,123
Isn't our friendship
deeper than that?

307
00:15:16,206 --> 00:15:17,750
I even backed you up earlier.

308
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,918
And now, you'll just
reject my heart?

309
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:22,921
Come on, don't be sad.

310
00:15:23,005 --> 00:15:25,382
Okay, fine. You're alright.

311
00:15:26,634 --> 00:15:27,718
"You're alright"?

312
00:15:27,801 --> 00:15:29,428
I'm just "alright"?

313
00:15:29,511 --> 00:15:31,472
You know what?
I'm more than that.

314
00:15:31,555 --> 00:15:32,890
I'm top-notch!

315
00:15:32,973 --> 00:15:34,516
Fine, then!

316
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,353
You're top-notch if you say so!

317
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:39,563
- Are we good now?
- [HUFFS]

318
00:15:39,647 --> 00:15:41,231
Whatever.

319
00:15:41,315 --> 00:15:42,983
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

320
00:15:43,067 --> 00:15:45,277
- Ouch.
- [STEPH] Wait, hold on.

321
00:15:45,361 --> 00:15:47,071
Sir Walter wouldn't
hide it here.

322
00:15:47,946 --> 00:15:50,866
- Where, then?
- Expect the unexpected, right?

323
00:15:50,949 --> 00:15:54,161
It's not here. Let's go.
This way. Come on.

324
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:56,830
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

325
00:15:56,914 --> 00:15:59,792
Baldo, search harder!
How are we going to win this?

326
00:16:01,001 --> 00:16:03,212
Hey, help me search!

327
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:05,673
- Uh, there's...
- What now?

328
00:16:05,756 --> 00:16:08,008
Charades? One word?

329
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:10,344
- Two syllables?
- I-It's a...

330
00:16:10,427 --> 00:16:11,762
- [SARAH] What?
- It's a beetle.

331
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:14,390
Beetle? [SCREAMS]

332
00:16:14,473 --> 00:16:16,517
It's a beetle!
Take it off of me!

333
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:18,936
- Take it off!
- Where's Kim Marie? Kim Marie!

334
00:16:19,019 --> 00:16:19,978
Kim Marie!

335
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:27,069
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

336
00:16:48,215 --> 00:16:51,635
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

337
00:16:51,719 --> 00:16:53,011
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

338
00:17:05,816 --> 00:17:07,985
[BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

339
00:17:08,068 --> 00:17:10,738
Take care of your heart,
Miss Sarah.

340
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:32,509
[RONI]
Sir Walter is unbelievable.

341
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:34,261
Why is he making us
search the woods?

342
00:17:36,972 --> 00:17:39,308
It's not here either.

343
00:17:39,391 --> 00:17:41,351
- Kim, where could it be?
- Roni!

344
00:17:42,394 --> 00:17:44,730
- Roni, Roni, Roni, look!
- Kim Marie, what is it?

345
00:17:44,813 --> 00:17:46,607
- Huh?
- Look!

346
00:17:46,690 --> 00:17:48,442
- There it is!
- Kim Marie!

347
00:17:48,525 --> 00:17:50,986
- We found it!
- We won!

348
00:17:52,988 --> 00:17:54,656
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

349
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:56,116
Go climb the tree.

350
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:58,035
Why me? You're the one
desperate to win.

351
00:17:58,118 --> 00:18:00,704
Do it before anyone else
takes it! Hurry!

352
00:18:00,788 --> 00:18:03,040
- Go, Roni! You can do it!
- [EXHALES]

353
00:18:03,123 --> 00:18:04,792
Go Roni! Let's go!

354
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:07,544
[CLAPPING] You can do it!

355
00:18:07,628 --> 00:18:09,463
- Just wait.
- Hurry! What are you doing?

356
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:11,882
[HUFFS]

357
00:18:11,965 --> 00:18:14,134
Hey! What are you doing?

358
00:18:14,218 --> 00:18:18,972
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

359
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:23,185
Roni, you just have to take it.
What are you doing?

360
00:18:23,268 --> 00:18:24,895
Come on, Roni.

361
00:18:24,978 --> 00:18:25,979
Here, Kim Marie.

362
00:18:27,439 --> 00:18:29,441
Handle it with care.

363
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:31,360
I don't want it to get dirty.

364
00:18:31,443 --> 00:18:33,570
Okay, fine. Just hurry up.

365
00:18:33,654 --> 00:18:34,446
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

366
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:36,323
Go, Roni! You can do it!

367
00:18:36,406 --> 00:18:38,492
Do it for the tablet! Let's go!

368
00:18:38,575 --> 00:18:40,869
[RONI] Help me out here.

369
00:18:40,953 --> 00:18:42,871
- One, two, three. You're heavy.
- [GRUNTS]

370
00:18:42,955 --> 00:18:44,581
[RONI] Here I go.

371
00:18:44,665 --> 00:18:45,999
Ouch.

372
00:18:46,083 --> 00:18:48,710
Okay. [GRUNTS]

373
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:50,170
Go get it! [LAUGHS]

374
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:51,922
- Just a bit more!
- Wait.

375
00:18:52,005 --> 00:18:54,758
Roni, you're almost there.
Last push!

376
00:18:54,842 --> 00:18:56,760
Wait. Wait, Kim Marie.

377
00:18:56,844 --> 00:18:59,596
- [GRUNTS]
- Just a bit more!

378
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:02,015
- [KIM MARIE] Okay! Go for it!
- I'm here.

379
00:19:02,099 --> 00:19:03,350
- It's so high!
- [KIM MARIE] Ah!

380
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:05,561
Oh my god! Kim Marie,
the tablet is ours!

381
00:19:05,644 --> 00:19:08,856
- [SHRIEKING]
- Oh my!

382
00:19:08,939 --> 00:19:10,232
It's so high, Kim Marie!

383
00:19:10,315 --> 00:19:12,651
I'll help you down.
Hurry!

384
00:19:12,734 --> 00:19:14,236
Kim Marie, help me!

385
00:19:14,319 --> 00:19:15,946
- It's so high! Oh my god!
- [PHONE RINGING]

386
00:19:16,029 --> 00:19:17,990
- Come here.
- Hurry! Just come down!

387
00:19:18,073 --> 00:19:19,616
[RONI] Kim Marie! Kim Marie!

388
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:21,618
- Hello?
- [RONI] Oh my god! Kim!

389
00:19:21,702 --> 00:19:23,954
- Hold on.
- Kim Marie, hey!

390
00:19:24,037 --> 00:19:27,666
Kim Marie, don't leave
my shirt on the ground!

391
00:19:27,749 --> 00:19:29,334
My shirt, Kim Marie!

392
00:19:29,418 --> 00:19:31,545
Kim Marie, where are you going?

393
00:19:31,628 --> 00:19:33,714
Kim Marie, it's so high!

394
00:19:33,797 --> 00:19:35,215
Kim Marie! Kim Marie!

395
00:19:35,299 --> 00:19:37,885
My shirt!

396
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:40,512
Ambulance! Call the ambulance!

397
00:19:43,098 --> 00:19:45,183
If you want the tablet,
then just say so.

398
00:19:46,268 --> 00:19:50,480
I can't do that, boss.
That's unfair to the others.

399
00:19:51,648 --> 00:19:53,859
The only reason why
I even agreed to this

400
00:19:53,942 --> 00:19:55,444
is so we could talk.

401
00:19:56,778 --> 00:19:59,698
[PHONE RINGING]

402
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:02,618
"Cyrus Castillo Incoming Call"

403
00:20:02,701 --> 00:20:05,829
[PHONE RINGING]

404
00:20:05,913 --> 00:20:07,581
Aren't you going to answer that?

405
00:20:07,664 --> 00:20:09,166
[PHONE RINGING]

406
00:20:09,249 --> 00:20:11,168
Boss!

407
00:20:11,251 --> 00:20:13,295
"Cyrus Castillo Call Declined"

408
00:20:13,962 --> 00:20:16,465
I don't want you talking
to my brother.

409
00:20:16,548 --> 00:20:18,717
Are you serious?

410
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:20,761
From now on,
if he wants to talk to you,

411
00:20:20,844 --> 00:20:22,721
then he has to go
through me, okay?

412
00:20:24,806 --> 00:20:26,642
[CLICKS TONGUE]
You know what, boss?

413
00:20:26,725 --> 00:20:28,727
I don't understand you.

414
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:32,648
What? I told you I'd court you
so you can't entertain anyone.

415
00:20:33,482 --> 00:20:36,068
Sir Cyrus isn't courting me.

416
00:20:36,151 --> 00:20:38,487
He's actually just
helping me remember

417
00:20:38,570 --> 00:20:40,155
what happened to me before.

418
00:20:40,238 --> 00:20:41,782
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

419
00:20:41,865 --> 00:20:43,116
What if I don't like it?

420
00:20:44,618 --> 00:20:46,745
Boss, with all due respect,

421
00:20:46,828 --> 00:20:48,497
I also have a personal life.

422
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:50,457
My life doesn't revolve
around my job.

423
00:20:50,540 --> 00:20:51,917
[KIM] So, whether
you approve it or not,

424
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,962
I'll do whatever I want.

425
00:20:55,045 --> 00:21:03,178
- [LEAVES RUSTLING]
- [PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

426
00:21:03,261 --> 00:21:04,596
Miss Sarah?

427
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:05,889
[PANTING]

428
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:07,307
Kim Marie!

429
00:21:07,391 --> 00:21:09,393
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

430
00:21:09,476 --> 00:21:10,811
Miss Sarah?

431
00:21:12,729 --> 00:21:15,691
- [RAIN POURING]
- [YELPS]

432
00:21:17,776 --> 00:21:18,860
Oh, no!

433
00:21:20,362 --> 00:21:23,907
[KIM PANTING]

434
00:21:23,991 --> 00:21:25,534
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

435
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:39,798
["IKAW SANA SIYA"
BY ANGELA KEN PLAYING]

436
00:22:06,950 --> 00:22:13,957
["IKAW SANA SIYA"
BY ANGELA KEN CONTINUES]

437
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:24,593
We're fine as it is.
We're good, right?

438
00:22:24,676 --> 00:22:25,677
We are?

439
00:22:25,761 --> 00:22:27,387
["UUWIAN" BY
JL AND BGYO PLAYING]

440
00:22:27,471 --> 00:22:31,141
- Hey, what are you doing?
- Keeping you from getting cold.

441
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:35,979
Everything's fine.

442
00:22:37,522 --> 00:22:40,067
Do you want things to get messy?

443
00:22:40,150 --> 00:22:41,485
Do you like me?

444
00:22:41,568 --> 00:22:43,361
Why do you ask?

445
00:22:43,445 --> 00:22:45,947
- Well?
- I like you just fine.

446
00:22:46,031 --> 00:22:48,742
Just fine? Oh, come on!

447
00:22:48,825 --> 00:22:50,619
I made a lot of people cry
in college.

448
00:22:50,702 --> 00:22:53,705
Baldo, we don't know
much about you.

449
00:22:53,789 --> 00:22:55,207
What type of girl do you like?

450
00:22:55,290 --> 00:23:01,254
Sweet, kind, and
most of all... cute.

451
00:23:01,338 --> 00:23:02,756
- [CHUCKLES]
- Hmm.

452
00:23:02,839 --> 00:23:04,966
By the way, when you
get back tomorrow,

453
00:23:05,050 --> 00:23:06,760
I'll have something amazing
prepared for you.

454
00:23:06,843 --> 00:23:13,850
["UUWIAN" BY
JL & BGYO CONTINUES]
